itemscroller.config.comment.carpetctrlqcraftingenabledonserver=Enable this if the server has the Carpet mod, and has the §ectrlQCrafting§r rule enabled.\n\nThis changes which method Item Scroller uses for the Drop key + Shift + Right click crafting. When enabled, the mod uses the better method that Carpet mod adds.
itemscroller.config.comment.clientcraftingfix1.12=Enables updating the crafting grid output slot directly on the client side.\n\nThis fixes any of the quick/mass craft features otherwise being broken in 1.12+, because in vanilla the client would have to wait for the server to sync the recipe output after each crafted item. The mod would then just see an empty slot immediately after moving the items to the grid, and would then abort the craft operation.
itemscroller.config.comment.craftingrecipessavefileglobal=When enabled, the recipe storage file is global, instead of being saved per-world or per-server
itemscroller.config.comment.craftingrecipessavetofile=Enables saving the Item Scroller recipe storage to a file at §a.minecraft/itemscroller/recipes_<worldorservername>.nbt§r. This makes the recipes persistent across game restarts.
itemscroller.config.comment.craftingrenderrecipeitems=Enables rendering the recipe ingredients for the stored recipes in the crafting recipe view (which is shown while holding the §eRecipe View§r key), and not just the recipe output item
itemscroller.config.comment.reversescrolldirectionsingle=Reverse the scrolling direction for the "move a single item" scroll move mode
itemscroller.config.comment.reversescrolldirectionstacks=Reverse the scrolling direction for the "move full stacks" scroll move mode
itemscroller.config.comment.slotpositionawarescrolldirection=When enabled, the item movement direction for the scroll move features depends on the slots' y-position on screen.\n\nMight be derpy with more complex inventories, so use with caution.
itemscroller.config.comment.villagertradelistrememberpage=Remember and restore the last looked at page/trade when opening the villager trade screen

itemscroller.config.comment.craftingfeatures=Enables scrolling items to and from crafting grids, with a custom crafting recipe storage.\n\nHold down the §eRecipe View§r key to see the recipe storage, to change the recipe selection and to store new recipes.\n\nWhile holding the §eRecipe View§r key, you can either scroll or press a number key to change the recipe selection. A recipe is stored to the currently selected "recipe slot" by using the §eStore Recipe§r hotkey while hovering over the crafting output slot's item.\n\nThe supported crafting grids must be added to the §eCrafting Grids§r list in the Lists config category.
itemscroller.config.comment.dropmatchingwithkey=Allows dropping all matching items to the hovered stack from the same inventory where the hovered stack is, by using the §eDrop All Matching§r hotkey
itemscroller.config.comment.modfeaturesenabled=Toggle all Item Scroller functionality ON/OFF
itemscroller.config.comment.rightclickcraftonestack=Allows crafting up to one full stack to the cursor when right clicking on a slot that has been configured as a crafting output slot.
itemscroller.config.comment.scrollmoveallmatching=Allows scroll moving all matching stacks at once while holding the §eMove Matching (modifier)§r hotkey
itemscroller.config.comment.scrollmoveentirestacks=Allows moving entire stacks at a time by scrolling over a stack.\n\nThe hovered stack is moved last, as otherwise you would have to move the cursor after each scroll.
itemscroller.config.comment.scrollmoveeverything=Allows scroll moving all items at once while holding the §eMove Everything (modifier)§r hotkey
itemscroller.config.comment.scrollmoveone=Allows moving items one item at a time by scrolling over a stack
itemscroller.config.comment.scrollstacksfallback=Enables a "fallback" mode for scrolling entire stacks.\n\nFor example the vanilla crafting table screen doesn't normally allow shift + clicking item to the grid. This fallback mode allows "manually" moving the stacks to the "other inventory".\n\nSo basically this is for any inventories where shift + click doesn't normally work.
itemscroller.config.comment.scrollvillager=Enables special handling for the Villager screen.\n\nNormally you can't shift click items in a villager trade screen. This feature enables single or full stack scroll features in a villager trade screen.\n\n(Hold shift and) scroll up/down over the trade output slot to move items in to the trade input slots and out from the trade output slot.
itemscroller.config.comment.shiftdropitems=Allows dropping all matching items at once (only from the inventory from which you picked up the stack from) by holding §eshift§r while clicking the stack from the cursor outside the inventory to drop the stack
itemscroller.config.comment.shiftplaceitems=Allows moving all matching stacks (only from the inventory from which you picked up the stack from) at once to the inventory where you are placing the stack from the cursor to, by holding §eshift§r while you place the stack from the cursor to an empty slot
itemscroller.config.comment.villagertradelist=Show a 1.14+ style trade list in the villager trade screens

itemscroller.config.comment.craftingscreens=A list of crafting screen definitions.\n\nThis defines which screens the crafting features can work in, and which slot is used as the output slot and which slots are used as the crafting grid slots.\n\nThe format is:\n  §ascreen_class,slot_class,output_slot,start_slot-end_slot§r\n\nSo for example:\n  §asome.mod.CraftingScreen,some.mod.CraftingSlot,0,1-9§r\n\nYou can find out the screen and slot class names and the slot numbers using the §eSlot Debug§r hotkey.
itemscroller.config.comment.guiblacklist=A list of inventory screens where Item Scroller shouldn't be active
itemscroller.config.comment.slotblacklist=A list of slots that Item Scroller should not operate on

