itemscroller.hotkey.comment.dragmoveone=Move one item from each stack dragged over while holding this hotkey
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.masscraft=Continuously "mass craft" and throw out the crafting result items for as long as this keybind is held down.\n\nThis uses the currently selected recipe (in the Item Scroller recipe storage).
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.movecraftresults=Move all of the currently selected recipe's (in the Item Scroller recipe storage) output items from the player inventory to the other inventory
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.moveeverything=Move §fALL§r items to the other inventory when clicking a stack
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.modifiermoveallmatching=Modifier key to hold while scrolling to move §fall matching§r items to the other inventory when scrolling over a stack
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.modifiermoveentirestack=Modifier key to hold while scrolling to move the entire stack to the other inventory when scrolling over it
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.modifiermoveeverything=Modifier key to hold while scrolling to move §fALL§r items to the other inventory when scrolling over a stack
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.movestacktooffhand=Swap the hovered stack with the offhand
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.openconfigscreen=Open the Item Scroller in-game config screen
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.showrecipes=Show the Item Scroller recipe storage area while holding this hotkey.\n\nNew recipes are stored by using the §eStore Recipe§r hotkey while hovering over the crafting grid output slot's item, while keeping this view open.\n\nYou can scroll up/down or use the up/down and (shift +) left/right arrow keys to change the selected recipe or recipe page.\n\nYou can left click on a recipe to move that recipe to the crafting grid, or right click to craft one stack using the recipe.
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.slotdebug=Print debug info about the hovered slot or inventory screen.\n\nTo print info about the inventory screen, use this hotkey while you are §dnot hovering§r over any inventory slots.
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.storerecipe=Store a recipe to the Item Scroller recipe storage, while hovering over a crafting grid's output item, and having the recipe view open by holding the §eRecipe View§r hotkey.
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.throwcraftresults=Throw all items from the player inventory matching the currently selected recipe's output item to the ground
itemscroller.hotkey.comment.villagertradefavorites=Trade everything possible with all of the favorited trades of the current villager
